<document>
	<title>Iodide-induced hypothyroidism without a goiter in an infant with
   cystic fibrosis.</title>

	<author>Rosenstein-B-J.</author>
	<author>Plotnick-L-P.</author>
	<author>Blasco-P-A.</author>

	<source>J-Pediatr. 1978 Aug. 93(2). P 261-2.</source>

	<abstract>It has been suggested that patients with cystic fibrosis may have an
   intrinsic abnormality of thyroid function that may be enhanced by
   the administration of iodides.  We wish to report an infant with CF
   in whom hyperthyroidism developed, in the absence of a goiter,
   following short-term iodide therapy.</abstract>

